  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I stop my Jamster subscription from charging me money?",
  "response": "To stop your Jamster subscription from charging you, you\u2019ll need to cancel the service. The exact process depends on how you signed up for the subscription. Here\u2019s a general guide to help you:\n\n### 1. **Check How You\u2019re Being Charged**\n   - **Mobile Phone Bill**: If the charges appear on your mobile phone bill, you likely signed up through your carrier.\n   - **Credit/Debit Card**: If the charges are on your card, you may have signed up directly through Jamster\u2019s website or app.\n\n### 2. **Cancel Through Your Mobile Carrier**\n   - **Text STOP**: Send a text message with the word **STOP** to the shortcode associated with Jamster (usually found in the terms or confirmation message).\n   - **Contact Customer Service**: Call your mobile carrier\u2019s customer service and request to cancel the Jamster subscription. They can block future charges.\n\n### 3. **Cancel Through Jamster\u2019s Website**\n   - Log in to your Jamster account if you created one during the sign-up process.\n   - Navigate to the subscription or account settings and look for a cancellation option.\n   - If you can\u2019t find it, contact Jamster\u2019s customer support for assistance.\n\n### 4. **Block Future Charges**\n   - Contact your **mobile carrier** to block premium SMS services or Jamster specifically.\n   - If charged to your **credit/debit card**, dispute the charge with your bank and ask them to block future transactions from Jamster.\n\n### 5. **Contact Jamster Directly**\n   - Visit Jamster\u2019s official website and look for their customer service contact information (email or phone).\n   - Request cancellation and confirmation in writing.\n\n### 6. **Monitor Your Billing**\n   - After cancellation, keep an eye on your phone bill or card statement to ensure no further charges are applied.\n\nIf you encounter difficulties, escalate the issue with your carrier or bank to ensure the subscription is fully cancelled.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
